                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.01476/2606.01476v1/figure/omniopd_diagram.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Overview ofOmniOPD.Entropy-Driven Chunk Selection:Given an input promptxx, the student model generates an on-policy trajectory.OmniOPDfirst identifies critical reasoning forks by locating local peaks in predictive entropy, selectively auditing only these high-uncertainty chunks.Chunk-level Teacher Critic:For each selected chunk, the trajectory prefixy<cy_{<c}is passed to the teacher model.\nThe teacher generatesNNMonte Carlo rollouts, which are then evaluated against the student’s generated chunk via a continuous semantic similarity metricϕ\\phi.Calculate Loss and Update Student:The student policy is updated by applying the distillation loss exclusively to the audited tokens.\nSimultaneously, a reference KL anchor is applied across the unaudited tokens to prevent policy shift.",
